    "faq": {
      "type": "aliange-pdp-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "q1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is Biocinamide and how does it work?",
            "answer": "<p>Biocinamide is a <strong>niacinamide-based corrective serum</strong> designed to regulate multiple skin functions simultaneously.</p><p>Niacinamide (vitamin B3) acts as a <strong>cellular regulator</strong>, helping to:</p><ul><li><br/>Reduce inflammation<br/></li><li><br/>Strengthen the skin barrier<br/></li><li><br/>Balance oil production<br/></li><li><br/>Improve overall skin clarity<br/></li></ul><p>It works by <strong>normalising how skin behaves</strong>, rather than targeting a single concern.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What skin concerns does Biocinamide target?",
            "answer": "<p>Biocinamide is designed to address:</p><ul><li><br/>Redness and inflammation<br/></li><li><br/>Acne and congestion<br/></li><li><br/>Uneven skin tone and pigmentation<br/></li><li><br/>Barrier dysfunction<br/></li><li><br/>Enlarged pores and excess oil<br/></li></ul><p>It is particularly effective where skin is <strong>reactive, imbalanced, or inconsistent</strong>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_GBrqpa": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I use Biocinamide with other active ingredients?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes—and this is where it performs best.</p><p>Niacinamide:</p><ul><li><br/>Enhances tolerance to actives like retinoids and acids<br/></li><li><br/>Reduces irritation from stronger treatments<br/></li><li><br/>Supports overall skin stability<br/></li></ul><p>This makes it an ideal <strong>foundation serum within a protocol system</strong>, not a standalone solution.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_PC3xKj": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long does it take to see results?",
            "answer": "<ul><li><strong>2–4 weeks:</strong> reduced redness, improved hydration, calmer skin<br/></li><li><br/><strong>4–8 weeks:</strong> clearer skin and more even tone<br/></li><li><br/><strong>8–12 weeks:</strong> improved skin stability and reduced recurrence of issues<br/></li></ul><p>Results reflect <strong>ongoing regulation of skin function</strong>, not quick suppression.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_kdePUT": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can Biocinamide help with rosacea or sensitive skin?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes.</p><p>Niacinamide is widely used in conditions involving:</p><ul><li><br/>Chronic inflammation<br/></li><li><br/>Barrier dysfunction<br/></li><li><br/>Sensitivity<br/></li></ul><p>It helps reduce inflammation and improve tolerance, making it beneficial for <strong>rosacea-prone or reactive skin types</strong>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does Biocinamide help with acne?",
            "answer": "<p>Niacinamide has <strong>clinically demonstrated anti-inflammatory effects</strong> and is widely used in acne treatment. </p><p>It works by:</p><ul><li><br/>Reducing inflammatory lesions<br/></li><li><br/>Regulating sebum production<br/></li><li><br/>Supporting clearer pores<br/></li></ul><p>This helps control breakouts <strong>without stripping or irritating the skin</strong>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does Biocinamide reduce redness?",
            "answer": "<p>Niacinamide has strong <strong>anti-inflammatory properties</strong>, which help calm:</p><ul><li><br/>Redness<br/></li><li><br/>Irritation<br/></li><li><br/>Reactive skin responses<br/></li></ul><p>It has been shown to <strong>reduce skin erythema (redness) and improve skin calmness</strong> with consistent use.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does Biocinamide improve the skin barrier?",
            "answer": "<p>Barrier dysfunction is a key driver of many skin concerns.</p><p>Niacinamide helps:</p><ul><li><br/>Increase ceramide production<br/></li><li><br/>Reduce water loss<br/></li><li><br/>Strengthen the outer skin layer<br/></li></ul><p>This leads to <strong>more resilient, stable skin over time</strong></p>"
          }
        }
      },
